## Basecamp
This project uses Basecamp, a structured development methodology.
- Core playbooks: `basecamp/playbooks/` (from repo root)
- Fiberco playbooks: `playbooks/` (from repo root)
- Playbooks are loaded automatically — invoke the Playbook tool before any work.

## Project Tracker
All work MUST be tracked. Before starting any work:
1. Run `tracker board --project {{PROJECT_NAME}}` to see current state
2. If resuming, run `tracker session-handoff {{PROJECT_NAME}}` for context
3. Create or pick a task, then `tracker session-start <code> "<objective>"`
4. During work, update session state with decisions, completions, blockers
5. Before ending, log next steps: `tracker session-update <code> --next "..."`

See `playbooks/project-tracking/PLAYBOOK.md` for full protocol.

## Tools
| Tool | Usage |
|------|-------|
| `project shell {{PROJECT_NAME}}` | Open shell in app container |
| `project db {{PROJECT_NAME}}` | Open psql in database |
| `project logs {{PROJECT_NAME}}` | Tail container logs |
| `tracker board` | View all tracked work |
| `tracker create "title" --project {{PROJECT_NAME}} --type feature` | Create a task |

## Infrastructure
- Reverse proxy: nginx on ports 80/443 with Let's Encrypt SSL
- DNS: Cloudflare A record for {{PROJECT_DOMAIN}}
- Docker network: `fiberco-internal` for inter-project communication
- Database is isolated (not on shared network) — only the app container can reach it

